				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Perhaps Nintendo put SRAM on Super NES PCBs in out-of-the-way address spaces because it didn't expect SRAM to be used for anything but battery save. The less time the save chip spends enabled, the less likely it is to suffer data loss when losing power or otherwise running out of voltage spec.</div>

