						<div class="postbody">wtf?<br /><br />No, what they would have told you was &quot;You don't want to waste your money buying a small amount of extra RAM on top of the 128 KiB that are already in the console&quot;.<br /><br />Historical production costs were huge, probably $10-$20 per unit, even in volume. Adding several more dollars on top of that wouldn't have been something you could have gotten anyone sane to finance.<br /><br />Also, the battery's presence wouldn't cause the game to <em>malfunction</em>, it would just mean that if you were using cart SRAM for something other than just save data, the save data was more likely to get destroyed.</div>

