					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">It uses 128kB of SRAM, but it's split up into 8kB banks because it is using an existing cartridge memory layout.  If you look carefully at the above code, I implemented an &quot;animation mode&quot; that is specifically for jumping across SRAM banks for rotating sprites.<br /><br /><div class="codetitle"><b>Code:</b></div><div class="codecontent">sram_bank_crossing:<br />lda {animation_index}<br />xba<br />and #$ff00<br />-;<br />cmp #$2000<br />bcc +<br />sbc #$2000<br />inc {temp2}<br />clc<br />bra -<br /><br />single_sprite:<br />lda $0002,y<br />bmi sram_bank_crossing<br />lda {animation_index}<br />xba<br />and #$ff00<br />clc<br />+;<br /></div></div>

